VERDICT (where first-task protection HOLDS vs BREAKS, single fixed knob set):
  AXIS 1 LENGTH    : separated-CI protection HOLDS at n_tasks in [3, 5, 8, 10]; forgetA creeps 0.038->0.124 over 3->10 tasks (mean still < always-plastic).
  AXIS 2 SIMILARITY: forgetA stays below always-plastic at ALL s (positive transfer at high s); the interference cost appears as the plastic-death tax, not as A-forgetting.
  AXIS 3 BUDGET    : separated-CI protection HOLDS at passes in [100, 150, 200] and BREAKS (CIs overlap) at passes in [300, 400, 600] -> CLEAN BREAK POINT ~passes 150->200.

  MECHANISM: the fuse consolidates A (theta->0, cbar~0.95) during A's passes, then needs the
  later tasks' surprise to re-erode c. With a FIXED tau_c/beta_c, a LARGER per-task budget gives
  B..E more erosion cycles on the shared synapses, so A's reserve is worn down faster than the
  knob set anticipates -> forgetA climbs until its CI overlaps always-plastic. The same knobs that
  protect at 100 passes no longer give a statistical guarantee at >=200. This IS spec FM4: a tuned
  knife-edge, not a proof -- protection-without-retuning is budget-bounded, not unconditional.
